          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@yahoo.com",
          "date": "2017-10-09 14:39:23.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
          "email": "mike.pershin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-10-24 09:14:26.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-8066 obd: migrate to ksets",
        "message": "LU-8066 obd: migrate to ksets\n\nLustre's sysfs only uses kobjects but with the introduction of\nksets we can use functionality like kset_find_kobj() and uevents.\nCurrently lustre is layered as lustre_kobj -> class -> obd device.\nThis patch changes the obd devices and the top level lustre_kobj\ninto ksets. The class level is kept as kobjects but are bound to\nthe top level lustre kset so they searchable and uevents can be\ncreated for them. Also much of the class functionality can be\nreplaced with what ksets can do. With obd devices now ksets we\ncan replace lprocfs_kset_register with lprocfs_obd_setup. Some\nof the sysfs attributes were not cleaned up so added proper\nremoval. Reversed what the default sysfs attributes are. This\nwill be needed for the replacement functionality for\nclass_process_proc_param().\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nChange-Id: I55fdd0aede66f3bdda302754dffe0ed982294082\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
